OL,3,GNorth East
OL,4,
OL,5,CThis Evening and Tonight:FCloudy but
OL,6,Fmostly dry to start. Light and patchy
OL,7,Frain arriving from the west during the
OL,8,Fevening, this becoming persistent and
OL,9,Foccasionally heavy overnight. Some
OL,10,Fsnow later on high ground. Becoming
OL,11,Fwindy, but this starting to ease
OL,12,Ftowards dawn.
OL,13,
OL,14,CSaturday:FEarly rain, with snow on
OL,15,Fhigh ground, clearing away eastwards
OL,16,Fby late morning. Sunny spells
OL,17,Fdeveloping, also blustery heavy
OL,18,Fshowers with a risk of thunder and
OL,19,Fsnow on high ground.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
